<subSubSection id="C37AC1F1020A4E2DA52FF9D163E5F787" pageId="2" pageNumber="257" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BDF927A020A4E2DA52FF9D16326F827" blockId="2.[854,1459,1567,2104]" pageId="2" pageNumber="257">
<emphasis id="B9144E68020A4E2DA52FF9D164C9F988" bold="true" box="[854,987,1567,1591]" pageId="2" pageNumber="257">Description</emphasis>
: Length of body 
<quantity id="4C983F9F020A4E2DA2C8F9EE6214F988" box="[1201,1286,1568,1592]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
; from anterior margin of head to posterior margin of elytra: about 
<quantity id="4C983F9F020A4E2DA52FF9AE64BEF9C8" box="[854,940,1632,1656]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
. Head without lateral grooves. Similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C60E9F9020A4E2DA52FF94E64EDF927" authority="Bordoni, 2017" authorityName="Bordoni" authorityYear="2017" box="[854,1023,1664,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Pachycorynus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="257" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kinabaluensis" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9144E68020A4E2DA52FF94E64EDF927" box="[854,1023,1664,1688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="257">P. kinabaluensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A227F313020A4E2DA274F94E6365F928" box="[1037,1143,1664,1687]" pageId="2" pageNumber="257" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
from which differs by the following characters: body (
<figureCitation id="135B8EFF020A4E2DA2ECF96E63F3F907" box="[1173,1249,1696,1720]" captionStart="Figs 28–31" captionStartId="7.[173,213,1707,1731]" captionTargetBox="[189,1950,584,1649]" captionTargetId="figure-101@7.[595,1075,559,1693]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 28–31: Habitus of Pachycorynus sabahensis spec. nov. (total lenght 5.4 mm) (28), P. balaneion spec.nov. (total lenght: 5 mm) (29) P. kinabaluensis spec. nov. (total lenght: 3.5 mm) (30) and Pachycorynus danum spec. nov. (total lenght: 3.5 mm) (31) (photo: S. Cuoco)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4754935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4754935/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="257">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
) very flat, brown, with yellowish antennae and legs; head longer and narrower, with smaller eyes and very fine and sparse punctation; pronotum broader, anteriad more dilated, with more oblique anterior margins, not sinuate sides and finer, sparser punctation; elytra narrower, with finer punctation; abdomen with transverse micro-striation and fine punctation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF927A020A4E2DA52FF86E63E5F787" blockId="2.[854,1459,1567,2104]" pageId="2" pageNumber="257">
Tergite and sternite of the male genital segment as in 
<figureCitation id="135B8EFF020A4E2DA52FF80E64D5F867" box="[854,967,1984,2008]" captionStart="Figs 1–12" captionStartId="5.[174,214,2052,2074]" captionTargetBox="[194,1401,1085,2033]" captionTargetId="figure-305@5.[174,1421,1070,2050]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1–12: Tergite and sternite of the male genital segment and aedeagus of Pachycorynus sabahensis spec. nov. (1–3), P. balaneion" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4754931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4754931/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="257">Figs 10-11</figureCitation>
. Aedeagus of peculiar shape (
<figureCitation id="135B8EFF020A4E2DA35DF80E627CF867" box="[1316,1390,1984,2008]" captionStart="Figs 1–12" captionStartId="5.[174,214,2052,2074]" captionTargetBox="[194,1401,1085,2033]" captionTargetId="figure-305@5.[174,1421,1070,2050]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 1–12: Tergite and sternite of the male genital segment and aedeagus of Pachycorynus sabahensis spec. nov. (1–3), P. balaneion" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4754931" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4754931/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="257">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) with broad and very short basal bulb; distal portion 
<quantity id="4C983F9F020A4E2DA32CF82E62A1F848" box="[1365,1459,2016,2040]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="2" pageNumber="257" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
long; parameres very narrow, shorter than the median lobe; inner sac with very minute scales.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37AC1F1020B4E2CA6D7FECE66BFFE87" pageId="3" pageNumber="258" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDF927A020B4E2CA6D7FECE66BFFE87" blockId="3.[174,779,256,312]" pageId="3" pageNumber="258">
